The paper deals with the estimation of entropy and entropy rate, which are fundamental concepts in information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of coding techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability). The paper also discusses the consistency and asymptotic unbiasedness of the estimator, which are topics typically studied in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
